response:
Yes, TypeSpec supports adding `description` and `externalDocs` to tags in the OpenAPI specification using the `@tagMetadata` decorator. This decorator allows you to specify additional metadata for tags, including a description and external documentation. Here's an example:

```typespec
@service
@tagMetadata(
  "Tag Name",
  #{
    description: "Tag description",
    externalDocs: #{ url: "https://example.com", description: "More info." },
    `x-custom`: "string",
  }
)
namespace PetStore {
}
```

This will generate the corresponding OpenAPI tag metadata with the `description` and `externalDocs` properties. You can use this feature to enhance the tags in your OpenAPI specification for better documentation and usability.

